## Docker Deployment Guide

### Prerequisites

- Docker 24+
- Docker Compose plugin
- 8 GB RAM recommended for running MongoDB, 10 Java services, and the frontend together
- Local ports `3000`, `27017`, and `8081` through `8090` available

### Step 1 - Review Docker Assets

This repository already includes the Docker deployment files:

- `docker/backend.Dockerfile`
- `docker/frontend.Dockerfile`
- `docker/nginx.conf`
- `docker-compose.yml`

### Step 2 - Build the Full Stack

```bash
docker compose build
```

If you want a clean rebuild without old layers:

```bash
docker compose build --no-cache
```

### Step 3 - Start All Containers

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Verify container status:

```bash
docker compose ps
```

### Step 4 - Verify the Deployment

Check the frontend:

```bash
curl http://localhost:3000
```

Check a few service health endpoints:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8081/api/v1/actuator/health
curl http://localhost:8084/api/v1/actuator/health
curl http://localhost:8090/api/v1/actuator/health
```

Open the application in your browser:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

### Step 5 - View Logs

```bash
docker compose logs -f frontend
docker compose logs -f auth-service
docker compose logs -f inventory-service
docker compose logs -f mongodb
```

### Step 6 - Stop, Restart, or Rebuild

Stop the stack:

```bash
docker compose down
```

Stop and remove MongoDB data volume too:

```bash
docker compose down -v
```

Rebuild one service and restart it:

```bash
docker compose build auth-service
docker compose up -d auth-service
```

Restart the whole stack:

```bash
docker compose restart
```

### Useful Docker Commands

```bash
# Container status
docker compose ps

# Follow all logs
docker compose logs -f

# Follow one service log
docker compose logs -f finance-billing-service

# Open shell inside a running container
docker compose exec auth-service sh

# Resource usage
docker stats
```

### Docker Troubleshooting

| Issue | Debug Command |
| --- | --- |
| Container exits immediately | `docker compose logs <service-name>` |
| Port already in use | `docker compose ps` and check local processes on `3000`, `27017`, `8081-8090` |
| MongoDB not reachable | `docker compose logs mongodb` |
| Frontend loads but API cards fail | `curl http://localhost:8081/api/v1/actuator/health` and `docker compose logs frontend` |
| Fresh reset needed | `docker compose down -v && docker compose up -d --build` |
